# .exportignore — LLM Wiki Template
# ====================================
# Patterns matched against export filenames.
# Files matching these patterns are excluded from the SQLite FTS5 index.
# They remain on disk as backup but are NEVER searchable.
#
# Format: one glob pattern per line (matched against filename only, not path).
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Add patterns for any sessions you want to archive but not index.
# Use --label to name sessions at export time:
#   python3 scripts/export-session.py --trigger manual --label client
# This produces: YYYY-MM-DD_HHMMSS_sessionid_manual_client.md
# Which matches: *_client_*.md

# ── Confidential (GPG-encrypted, never plaintext in index) ───────────────────
*_confidential_*.md

# ── Common sensitive categories (uncomment what applies to you) ───────────────
# *_client_*.md
# *_nda_*.md
# *_legal_*.md
# *_medical_*.md
# *_personal_*.md
# *_financial_*.md
# *_jobsearch_*.md
# *_interview_*.md
